  1. Axis deviation Left axis deviation suggests VT. (Extreme "north-west" axis. Source
    1. Capture beats - a normal shaped QRS complex when an SA node impulse captures the ventricles.
    2. Fusion beats: sinus and ventricular beat occur simultaneously (QRS morphology is intermediate VT beat and sinus beat)
  2. Positive OR negative concordance
  3. AND

  4. RSR’ complexes with a taller “left rabbit ear”. This is the most specific finding in favour of VT. This is in contrast to RBBB, where the right rabbit ear is taller

Drugs for acute management of SVT

  1. Amiodarone - more effective than lidocaine. Source
    1. Can use even in heart failure
  2. Lidocaine
  3. Procainamide

  • Pathogenesis of Sjogren's: Autoimmune disease affecting exocrine glands.
  1. Extra glandular symptoms
  • A severely affected patient may have florid salivary gland enlargement, adenopathy, antibodies to the Ro/SSA and La/SSB antigens, cryoglobulinemia, hypocomplementemia, a propensity to develop non-Hodgkin lymphoma, and other extraglandular disease manifestations.
  • 90% are positive for Rheumatoid factor: Kumar and Clark
  • Epidemiology: Most Commonly occurs in women aged 50-60 years old.
    • Characterized by sudden onset dry mouth leading to difficulty in swallowing.
    1. Dialysis-related amyloidosis (DRA) is a disabling disease characterized by accumulation and tissue deposition of amyloid fibrils consisting of beta2-microglobulin (beta2-m) (Aβ2M) in the bone, periarticular structures, and viscera of patients with end-stage kidney disease. Beta2-m is a component of the major histocompatibility complex that is present on cell surfaces and is normally cleared by glomerular filtration
    2. Aβ2M amyloidosis presents with carpal tunnel syndrome.

Source

  • Tingling in extremeties -> peripheral neuropathy (mnemonic: mechanics in the image -> have course hands -> they feel numb)
- Also of note, in post menopausal females, most of the oestrogen is produced by peripheral aromatization of androgens. [Source](https://www.researchgate.net/figure/Peripheral-aromatization-of-androgens-to-oestrogens-represents-the-principal-source-of_fig2_226077470)
    - So aromatase inhibitors like anastrozole and letrozole are used in treatment in ER+ve breast cancer.

  • Signs and symptoms of strokes.
    • Homocystaenaemia is a related condition which presents with early strokes.
  • Unprovoked DVT at young age
    • There are 3 types of homocystinuria depending on the genetic defect:
      • deficiency in the cystathionine B-synthase (CBS) enzyme,
      • defective methylcobalamin synthesis,
      • or abnormality in methylene tetrahydrofolate reductase (MTHFR).
  • ⭐Cyanide-nitroprusside test is positive. It is done on the urine to detect sulfur containing amino acids; Not sensitive or specific.
  • Blood levels for homocysteine can be done. Samples must be transported on ice and spun within 1 hour.

Phenylketonuria

Source

  • The most common inborn error of amino acid metabolism.
  • aka phenylalanine hydroxylase deficiency.
  • There is inability to metabolise phenylalanine.
  • Intellectual impairment is the most distinguishing feature.
  • 50% have epilepsy.
  • Extrapyramidal manifestations+
  • Fair skin and fair hair due to impairment of melanin synthesis. Treatment will restore pigmentation.
  • Management
    • Dietary: Avoid "These foods are high protein foods, such as milk, dairy products, meat, fish, chicken, eggs, beans, and nuts." Source
    • Medical:
      • Sapropterin - acts as a cofactor for the deficient enzyme
      • Pegvaliase - Pegylated enzyme replacement.
